===Etymology===
Old English ''[[poudre]]'', ''[[pouldre]]'', French ''[[poudre]]'', Old French also ''[[poldre]]'', ''[[puldre]]'', Latin ''[[pulvis]]'', ''[[pulveris]]'': cf. [[pollen]] fine flour, mill dust, E. pollen. Cf. {[[polverine]]}, {[[pulverize]]}.

===Pronunciation===
\Pow"der\

*{{audio|en-us-powder.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aʊdə(r)|-aʊdə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# The fine particles to which any dry substance is reduced by pounding, grinding, or triturating, or into which it falls by decay; dust.
#:''Grind their bones to powder small.''  &mdash;Shakespeare
# An explosive mixture used in gunnery, blasting, etc.; [[gunpowder]].

